\title{Hypothesis error}

\p{
In any binary hypothesis testing problem, a test #{ P_{Z|X|} } can incur two types of errors:
##{\begin{align*}
   \pi_{1|0}(P_{Z|X})&=\mathbb{P}_{H_{0}}\ (Z=1) \quad \text{(type-I error of false alarm rate)} \\
 \pi_{01}(P_{Z|X})&=\mathbb{P}_{H_{1}}\ (Z=0) \quad  \text{(type-II error or missed detection rate)}
.\end{align*}}
}
